premise_source_doc_sentence: Propelled to international success by social media , One Direction 's five albums , Up All Night  (  2011  )  , Take Me Home  (  2012  )  , Midnight Memories  (  2013  )  , Four  (  2014  )  , and Made in the A.M.  (  2015  )  , topped charts in most major markets , and generated hit singles including `` What Makes You Beautiful '' , `` Live While We 're Young '' , `` Best Song Ever '' , `` Story of My Life '' , and `` Drag Me Down '' .

The album 's number-one debut on the US Billboard 200 chart made One Direction the first group to bow atop the Billboard 200 with their first two albums since American girl group Danity Kane entered with Welcome to the Dollhouse in 2008 and their self-titled debut in 2006 .
The album was preceded by its lead single `` Best Song Ever '' and its critically acclaimed second single `` Story of My Life '' .
Their next album , Made in the A.M. , was preceded by its lead single `` Drag Me Down '' .
